==English==

===Etymology===
Germanic ''adal'' (noble) + ''berht'' (bright); {{ang}} ''Aeþelbeorht''. It became very popular in 19th century England due to Queen Victoria’s consort, Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha.

===Proper noun===
'''Albert'''

